address: 51 Kensington Church Street, London W8 4BA, United Kingdom
author: Dana P.
description:
One of our favorite meals of our recent trip to London.
From the moment we walked in we felt like we were at a friends house 
 for dinner. Outstanding food. We had the Lamb and Fish and chips.
Both were some of the best ever. Ffiona the owner was present and 
really made a great effort to make our evening memorable.Also our server
 a young lady from Portugal (I'm sorry I didn't get her name) was great.
I can see why shes been in business for 25 years. Great job !!
